d":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/mourning-and-funeral-customs-in-turkiye.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/mourning-and-funeral-customs-in-turkiye.webp","width":"1168","height":"880","caption":"Traditional Turkish funeral wreath and symbols","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/mourning-and-funeral-traditions-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/mourning-and-funeral-traditions-in-turkey/","name":"Mourning and Funeral Customs in Turkey","datePublished":"2026-02-03T15:35:16+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:39:13+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/mourning-and-funeral-customs-in-turkiye.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Mourning and Funeral Customs in Turkey","keywords":"Funeral","datePublished":"2026-02-03T15:35:16+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T21:39:13+03:00","articleSection":"Cultural Adaptation","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Learn about mourning and funeral traditions in Turkey. Click now to learn more about these traditions!","name":"Mourning and Funeral Customs in Turkey","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/mourning-and-funeral-traditions-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/mourning-and-funeral-traditions-in-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/mourning-and-funeral-customs-in-turkiye.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/mourning-and-funeral-traditions-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey, with its rich cultural background and diverse belief systems, is a country rich in mourning and funeral traditions. In this article, we will discuss the importance of mourning and funeral traditions in Turkey, the traditional practices involved in funerals, the role of family and society in the mourning process, as well as the expressions used in the mourning process and their meanings.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="the-importance-of-mourning-and-funeral-traditions-in-turkey">The Importance of Mourning and Funeral Traditions in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Mourning and funeral traditions form an important part of the cultural and social fabric of a society. In Turkey, these traditions have been shaped under the influence of both Islam and local beliefs. These traditions are practiced to perpetuate the memory of the deceased, to bring the family and community together and to support the grieving process.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Funerals reinforce a sense of unity and solidarity in society, while the mourning process provides an opportunity to share the pain of loss and grieve together. This contributes to the emotional healing process of individuals.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="traditional-practices-in-funeral-ceremonies">Traditional Practices in Funeral Ceremonies</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Funeral ceremonies in Turkey are enriched by various traditional practices. These practices may vary according to local culture and beliefs, but generally include the following elements:</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Washing and Shrouding:</strong> The body is first washed and shrouded by members of the same sex in accordance with religious rules. These procedures are usually carried out in gasilhanas in mosque courtyards or in private areas, with the cooperation of trained attendants and family members.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Funeral Prayer:</strong> According to Islamic belief, performing the funeral prayer means praying for the soul of the deceased. This prayer can be performed in mosques or funeral homes.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Burial Ceremony:</strong> The body is usually buried in the family cemetery or in a designated grave. During the burial, prayers are recited and blessings are said for the soul of the deceased.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Condolence Visits: </strong><span style="font-size: inherit;background-color: var(--base-3);color: var(--contrast)">After the funeral, relatives visit the bereaved family to offer condolences and moral support. During these visits, it is essential not to leave the family alone with examples of solidarity, such as taking food or sweets to the family, as well as meeting practical needs.</span></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can also take a look at <a title="Birth and Child Raising Traditions in Turkey" href="https://roadtostudy.com">Traditions of Birth and Child Raising in Turkey</a>.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="support-in-the-grief-process-the-role-of-family-and-society">Support in the Grief Process: The Role of Family and Society</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The grieving process is a very difficult time for individuals. The support of the family and the community contributes greatly to the emotional healing process of the bereaved. Family members support each other, share the pain of loss and grieve together. Neighbors and friends also provide various forms of assistance to support the grieving family.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Society&#8217;s support during the grieving process helps to strengthen social ties and make individuals feel better. In Turkey, condolence dinners after a funeral are organized to give morale to the grieving family and social solidarity comes to the fore in this process.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="expressions-used-in-the-mourning-process-in-turkey-and-their-meanings">Expressions Used in the Mourning Process in Turkey and Their Meanings</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some frequently used expressions and their meanings in Turkish culture during the mourning process are as follows:</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>My condolences:</strong> This expression is used to express condolences to the bereaved.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>God have mercy on you:</strong> This expression is used to pray for the soul of the deceased.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Rest in peace:</strong> This expresses the wish for the soul of the deceased to rest in peace.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Reading Yasin:</strong> Yasin is a surah of the Holy Qur&#8217;an and is recited after a funeral as a gift to the soul of the deceased.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These phrases are used to provide emotional support during the grieving process and to share the loss.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="remembering-together-healing-together">Remembering Together, Healing Together</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Mourning and funeral traditions in Turkey reflect the cultural richness and spirit of solidarity of the society. These traditions are practiced to honor the memory of the deceased, to bring the family and community together and to support the grieving process. Family and community support helps the grieving process to be handled in a healthy way, and the expressions used reinforce the emotional dimension of this process. These traditions in Turkey contribute to the emotional healing process of both individuals and communities, providing an opportunity for reunion and solidarity in the wake of loss.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-do-funerals-take-place-in-turkey">How do funerals take place in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Funerals in Turkey usually consist of washing, shrouding, funeral prayers and burial.</p>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is the role of family and society in the grieving process?</h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Family and community provide emotional support, opportunities to grieve together, and solidarity during the grieving process.</p>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is the purpose of condolence dinners after a funeral?</h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Condolence dinners are organized to provide morale and support to the bereaved family.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-are-the-expressions-used-in-the-mourning-process">What are the expressions used in the mourning process?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Commonly used expressions during the mourning process include &#8220;I&#8217;m sorry for your loss&#8221;, &#8220;May God have mercy on you&#8221; and &#8220;May his place be in heaven&#8221;.</p>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What traditional practices are found in funeral ceremonies?</h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Funeral ceremonies include traditional practices such as washing and shrouding, funeral prayers, burial and condolence visits.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2026-02-03T12:35:16Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-15T18:39:13Z', "featured_image" = '{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/mourning-and-funeral-customs-in-turkiye.webp","alt":"Traditional Turkish funeral wreath and symbols","title":"mourning-and-funeral-customs-in-turkiye"}' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'mourning-and-funeral-traditions-in-turkey';
