<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>My condolences:</strong> This expression is used to express condolences to the bereaved.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>God have mercy on you:</strong> This expression is used to pray for the soul of the deceased.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Rest in peace:</strong> This expresses the wish for the soul of the deceased to rest in peace.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Reading Yasin:</strong> Yasin is a surah of the Holy Qur&#8217;an and is recited after a funeral as a gift to the soul of the deceased.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These phrases are used to provide emotional support during the grieving process and to share the loss.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="remembering-together-healing-together">Remembering Together, Healing Together</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Mourning and funeral traditions in Turkey reflect the cultural richness and spirit of solidarity of the society. These traditions are practiced to honor the memory of the deceased, to bring the family and community together and to support the grieving process. Family and community support helps the grieving process to be handled in a healthy way, and the expressions used reinforce the emotional dimension of this process. These traditions in Turkey contribute to the emotional healing process of both individuals and communities, providing an opportunity for reunion and solidarity in the wake of loss.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-do-funerals-take-place-in-turkey">How do funerals take place in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Funerals in Turkey usually consist of washing, shrouding, funeral prayers and burial.</p>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is the role of family and society in the grieving process?</h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Family and community provide emotional support, opportunities to grieve together, and solidarity during the grieving process.</p>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is the purpose of condolence dinners after a funeral?</h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Condolence dinners are organized to provide morale and support to the bereaved family.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-are-the-expressions-used-in-the-mourning-process">What are the expressions used in the mourning process?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Commonly used expressions during the mourning process include &#8220;I&#8217;m sorry for your loss&#8221;, &#8220;May God have mercy on you&#8221; and &#8220;May his place be in heaven&#8221;.</p>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What traditional practices are found in funeral ceremonies?</h3>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Funeral ceremonies include traditional practices such as washing and shrouding, funeral prayers, burial and condolence visits.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2026-02-03T12:35:16Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-15T18:39:13Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/mourning-and-funeral-customs-in-turkiye.webp","alt":"Traditional Turkish funeral wreath and symbols","title":"mourning-and-funeral-customs-in-turkiye"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'mourning-and-funeral-traditions-in-turkey' );
